There once lived two twin brothers, Josh and Jordan Bell, whose hearts beat as one to the rhythm of the basketball court, and though they were but young lads, their skill with the ball was renowned. Their father, a legend of the game, imparted wisdom and fierce love, while their mother, wise and stern, guided their minds. But as the boys grew, shadows began to lengthen across their harmonious court. For Jordan found affection in a young maiden, drawing his focus from their shared passion, and more gravely, a hidden ailment began to weaken their beloved father. Thus, young Josh found himself adrift, grappling with jealousy, the changing bonds of brotherhood, and a profound fear for the man who taught them all they knew.
